To run the analysis in lxplus, afs-visible area (not tmp directory):
====================================================================

0) Modifications:
------------------

Modify the following files, if needed:

* HPlusHadronic_x.txt	rates & uncertainties for mH=x
* input_luminosity	luminosity shown in plots

You may also want to use other datacards than HPlusHadronic_x.txt; in this 
case copy them to the directory and write the names to script_run_LandS 

1) compile the modified LandS software
------------------------------------------------------------------------

go to the current directory (test/brlimit)

cvs co UserCode/mschen/LandS OR cvs co -r t3-03-10_ChargedHiggs UserCode/mschen/LandS
cd UserCode/mschen/LandS  
cmsenv
gmake clean; gmake all;
cd ../../..

Sidenote:
 This LandS version is modified by Mingshui 5.7.2011
 Suggested use:

==
lands.exe  --PhysicsModel ChargedHiggs  -M Hybrid
--bQuickEstimateInitialLimit 0 --initialRmin 0. --initialRmax 0.05  -d
HPlusHadronic_120.txt
 
To calculate expectation bands:
add option "--doExpectation 1 -t xxx"  where xxx is the number of toys
(1000 recommended ).
==


2) run LandS (takes some time; you may skip this and directly make 
the plots with the presaved values in output files if you want don't want 
to run LandS again).  Note that you can start one LandS job, then change
the datacard name, and restart another job without waiting.
-------------------------------------------------------------

(Recommendation: "rm output*" before running the script)

./script_run_LandS

*As a result, files output_LandS_HPlusHadronic_* are (re)generated


3) run the ROOT analysis to obtain Br limit (mH,Br)
---------------------------------------------------

root -l -b -q brlimit.cxx
you have to insert by hand the name of the output files to use 
(e.g. output_LandS_HPlusHadronic)

*As a result, the br limit plot brlimits.png/eps is generated

*if no appropriate data exists, a point in BR=0 is plotted; to remove this,
hard-coded values of nData and mH


4) run the python analysis to obtain MSSM limit (mH,tanB)
---------------------------------------------------------

cmsenv
./mssmLimit.py

*As a result, the tanb limit plots mssmLimits.png/eps and mssmLimits_mus.png/eps are generated
*you may want to toggle the setting "useMA" to show results in mA,tanb space, or the setting
 "showTeva" and "showLEP" to show/hide Tevatron and LEP results


Possible problems:
------------------

* no output files: 
  -check that you are in lxplus, and your working area can be 
   accessed by afs:  do not use a /tmp/ directory